          "email": "alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com",
          "date": "2015-02-27 14:28:26.000000000",
          "tz": 180
        },
        "subject": "LU-5319 ptlrpc: atomically assign XID and put on the sending list",
        "message": "LU-5319 ptlrpc: atomically assign XID and put on the sending list\n\nit's required to have all assigned XIDs on the sending list so\nwe can learn the lowest active XID at any point. this is in turn\nrequired to be able to report the highest replied XID to the server\nso the server can release corresponding slots in last_rcvd.\n\nuse that value to calculate the highest XID the server won't get.\nthis value is sent to the server.\n\ncurrently XIDs are generated way ahead of actual sending, so it's\neasily possible that the sending list doesn't list all XIDs in flight\nor to be sent.\n\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly mdtfilesystemtype=ldiskfs mdsfilesystemtype=ldiskfs \\\nostfilesystemtype=ldiskfs envdefinitions=SLOW=yes\n\nChange-Id: I1ece2f1806386a657a9a57d4fc3c8ffb2f32b47a\nSigned-off-by: Alex Zhuravlev <alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
